The &#39;annotations&#39; of a CrawlURI are (whitespace-free) strings that are 
appended, separated by commas, as the last whitespace-delimited field of 
the crawl.log line. See CrawlURI.addAnnotation().

But, this mechanism isn&#39;t very robust and if heavily used by different 
projects could run into problems.

I&#39;ve been wondering if we need a more general add-what-you-need option 
for the crawl.log; perhaps the last item on each line could be an 
arbitrarily-extendible JSON string -- either with no newlines or with 
some newline-escaping/continuation convention? (Or is there a better 
practice we could borrow from another project?)

